lenders.name: christopher styles
lenders.loan_because: Hi i am a 30 year old professional Barber living in the great northwest.  My passion in life since i was 12 yo is cutting and styling men and boys hair. I learned at a early age the power of looking good and feeling good about urself.  Something as small as a 15 minute haircut can boost one's self confidence to achieve their goals  or motivate that person to start working  towards them. That is exactly how i felt the day i got my first professional haircut in a barbershop. Alot of my peers and especially the kids need more places to go to afterschool, on the weekend, or just to get away from their neighborhoods  that will motivate and teach them the importance and the right path to becoming a productive and respected member of their community, city, and country.  Since i have been out of work i have been stopping by community centers and senior centers giving discounted haircuts. My clientel is picking up and driving across town 2 or 3 times a day is starting to take a toll on my vehicle (gas), and as well as my energy.  I have found a building that is perfect for my business. Its right across from an elemetry school and up the street from a senior center i have volunteered at. I feel having this building would allow me the room and security i need to continue barbering.  I'm praying to raise the cost of the down payment wich is $3000.  I have the clientel to keep up with the mortgage so that wouldnt be a problem. I have had a few stars on my rosterin the past when they lived in Seattle like, nfl players like: shawn alexander, seneca wallace and dyral jackson, nba players like shawn kemp, avery johnson, nate mcmillian, rashard lewis and a couple a music artist like warren g.  as well as ray j.   So if u can help a young entrepunuer from seattle get my business of the grown it would be greatly appreciated (and paid back fully)!!!!! Thanx so much for taking the time out to hear my story.  GOD bless!

It's a three step organization to help domestic violence survivors with indivdual, family and group therapies to get them out of the violence and to stay out.
